NUMBER 3606
  NAME Mansion Stairway
  *DESCRIPTION_START
You are standing atop a dank, musty stairway, gray stone walls closing in all around. A single, sputtering torch faintly illuminates your surroundings, yet provides no hint as to what lies below.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  FIXED_LIGHT
  EXIT O 322
  ITEM 0 81  VAL2=3607
  IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The dusty air almost makes you cough.
    ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You hear the distant sound of tiny scuffling feet, but can't quite place the source.
  ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3607
  NAME Wine Cellar
  *DESCRIPTION_START
You have entered the mansion's wine cellars, row upon row of carefully labeled bottles, a testimony to the decadence of the mansion's inhabitants. Softly glowing lanters provide a subtle illumination. A rough stack of wooden crates lies haphazardly against the far wall. Geoffrey, an ancient man in a faded tuxedo, stands here, keeping watch over the wines. A stairway leads back into the mansion proper.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  FIXED_LIGHT
  ITEM 0 539
  ITEM 1 828  ADJ1=355
  ITEM 2 420
  ITEM 7 81  VAL2=3606
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The old wooden racks are full of darkened bottles of wine.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  IFENTRY
    IFVAR ORG = 8
      ECHO ALL Geoffrey says, "Good day %N. How good it is to see you again."
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ORG ! 8
      ECHO ALL Geoffrey stares coldly at %N and says, "May I help you?"
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB TAP 2
    IFVAR ORG ! 8
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO ALL Geoffrey glares at %N and says, "Sir, I am afraid you will have to leave."
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB KILL -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER Geoffrey frowns at you, and snaps his fingers.
    ECHO OTHERS Geoffrey frowns at %N, and snaps his fingers.
    ECHO ALL Two burly men appear, grab the offender, and haul them outside.
    POSITION SIT
    MOVE 322
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB CAST -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER Geoffrey shakes his head at you and says, "We'll have none of that in here."
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PROJECT -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER Geoffrey shakes his head at you and says, "We'll have none of that in here."
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB GO 1
    CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ORG = 8
      ECHO PLAYER You feel around for the familiar opening, and enter the guild hall proper.
      ECHO OTHERS %N taps at the far wall, and vanishes amidst the crates.
      MOVE 323
      AFFECT 323
      ECHO OTHERS %N arrives through a concealed opening.
      AFFECT 3607
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ORG ! 8
      ECHO PLAYER You feel around amidst the crates as Geoffrey eyes you disapprovingly, but don't find anything.
      ECHO OTHERS %N fumbles around in the crates.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
    ECHO PLAYER You smell the strong, pungent odor of ageing wine.
  ENDIF
  IFSAY ADMIT
    IFVAR ORG = 8
      IFVAR ORGRANK > 199
        ECHO PLAYER You admit everyone in the room into the guild hall.
        ECHO ALL Several burly guards appear, and escort you into the Rake's hall.
        MOVEALL 323
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFSAY WINE
    IFVAR ORG = 8
      IFITEM 3
        ECHO PLAYER Geoffrey says, "You'll have to take the glass that's there, first."
      ENDIF
      IFNOITEM 3
        ECHO PLAYER Geoffrey nods to you, placing a glass of wine on the ground before you.
        ECHO OTHERS Geoffrey fetches %N a glass of wine.
        NEWITEM 3 546
        NEWPUT 3 237  VAL3=5
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ORG ! 8
      ECHO PLAYER Geoffrey raises an eyebrow towards you questioningly.
      ECHO OTHERS Geoffrey raises an eyebrow towards %N questioningly.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3608
  NAME Office of the Guildmaster, Stefan
  *DESCRIPTION_START
A confusing melange of symbols confronts your vision. The centerpiece of the room is obviously a large wooden desk, with a strange rune painted on the front. A colorful mural has been painted on one wall, and a huge bookcase rests against the opposite wall. Standing on the floor, just before the desk is a statue of a great warrior. A titanium door provides egress.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  ASTRAL
  FIXED_LIGHT
  ITEM 0 346
  ITEM 1 1481
  ITEM 2 201
  ITEM 3 1028
  ITEM 4 943  ADJ1=328  VAL2=323  VAL3=3608
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
This is a life size replica in gold of Orlin Thinvar, hero of Fayd. He stands proudly, raising his gleaming sword as if to smite some hideous demonic foe, the symbol of Rorin adorning his shining breastplate.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The mural depicts a beautifully painted silver oak against a deep blue sky, with small white clouds drifting past. On many of the branches have been inscribed names of the Thinvar family, though this part of the mural appears to be incomplete.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Looking at the desk, you are reminded of certain theories on the nature of chaos. Specifically, that even in the greatest of chaos, there is always some kind of underlying order. Even so here. Stacks of papers are strewn about everywhere, though is some sort of vague chronological order. The rune on the front seems to be mystical in nature, though its exact purpose is unclear.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
Scanning the spines, you see such titles as, "Stealth as Victory", "The Art of War", "A Military History of Fayd", and "Wizardry, Witchcraft and Swordplay"
  *DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 3609
  NAME Office of the Grandmaster, Thalion
  *DESCRIPTION_START
A large desk sits in the center of the room covered with stacks of unfinished paperwork. Sitting atop the desk is a brass nameplate and a small portrait. A shield and crossed rapiers hang on the wall behind the desk and a tapestry hangs from another. The floor is carpeted with a thick rug and a bookshelf sits in the corner. The walls are paneled in a warm wood motif and a fireplace, apparently connected to the Mansion above, illuminates the room from a corner.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  ASTRAL
  FIXED_LIGHT
  EXIT O 323
  ITEM 0 1548
  ITEM 1 250
  ITEM 2 277
  ITEM 3 1592
  ITEM 4 86
  ITEM 5 201
  ITEM 6 1308
  ITEM 7 943  ADJ1=328  VAL2=323  VAL3=3609
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The shield is emblazoned with a silver image of the Great Oak, the symbol of Shemri, and is rimmed with polished elkyri.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The tapestry is a depiction of Thalion leading the charge up Black Mountain, his rapier flashing in the sunlight as he throws himself against the forces of Siryx. Dragons, nightsteeds, and ravagers lay dying as the adventurers battle to glory.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The bookshelf is lined with texts on combat, stealth, and strategy. Titles include Sun Tzu's 'The Art of War', Bergommen's 'Fight Smart, Not Hard', and Vintigo's 'Complete Book of Rapiers'.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 3
The nameplate reads:    Thalion the Grey
                        Servant of Shemri
                       Aelfen Blademaster
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  *DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
Amidst all the papers is an unfinished manuscript entitled "The Art of Swordsmanship by Thalion the Grey" complete with illustrations and diagrams.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
