    ECHO PLAYER You hear a strange whistling sound, far away.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PULL 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO OTHERS %N pulls back on %a.
    ECHO PLAYER You pull back on %a.
    IFVAR CHASGATE = 1
      ECHO ALL Nothing happens.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR CHASGATE = 0
      ECHO ALL An opening in the floor slides open.
      NEWITEM 8 72  VAL2=3613
      EQUAL CHASGATE 1
      AFFECT 3613
      ECHO ALL An opening appears in the ceiling.
      NEWITEM 8 72  VAL2=3612
      AFFECT 3612
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PUSH 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You push %a.
    ECHO OTHERS %N pushes %a.
    IFVAR CHASGATE = 0
      ECHO ALL Nothing happens.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR CHASGATE = 1
      ECHO ALL The opening in the floor slides shut.
      REMOVEITEM 8
      EQUAL CHASGATE 0
      AFFECT 3613
      ECHO ALL The opening in the ceiling slides shut.
      REMOVEITEM 8
      AFFECT 3612
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
NUMBER 3613
  NAME A Nexus of Passageways
  *DESCRIPTION_START
Three nondescript dirt passages come together here, forming a junction. A loose grate covers a foul-smelling hole in the floor, next to which a rope ladder is coiled. A large metal lever juts up from the floor here as well.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  FIXED_LIGHT
  EXIT S 3615
  EXIT SE 3616
  EXIT W 3617
  ITEM 0 79  ADJ1=87  VAL2=3614
  ITEM 1 1108
  ITEM 2 641  ADJ1=192
  EXTEND 0 which smells really bad
  EXTEND 1 made of knotted ropes
  IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You hear what sounds like wind, far away, whistling through various passages.
    ECHO OTHERS %N listens to %h surroundings.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The foul stench from the hole pretty much overpowers anything else you might otherwise be able to smell here.
    ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB RECALL -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER This place sort of vaugely fits certain rumors you've heard about a secret dungeon beneath the city connecting several key locations.
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PULL 2
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You pull back on %a.
    ECHO OTHERS %N pulls back on %a.
    IFVAR CHASGATE = 0
      ECHO ALL Nothing happens.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR CHASGATE = 1
      ECHO ALL The opening in the ceiling slides shut.
      REMOVEITEM 8
      EQUAL CHASGATE 0
      AFFECT 3612
      ECHO ALL The opening in the floor slides shut.
      REMOVEITEM 8
      AFFECT 3613
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PUSH 2
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You push %a.
    ECHO OTHERS %N pushes %a.
    IFVAR CHASGATE = 1
      ECHO ALL Nothing happens.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR CHASGATE = 0
      ECHO ALL An opening in the ceiling slides open.
      NEWITEM 8 72  VAL2=3612
      EQUAL CHASGATE 1
      AFFECT 3612
      ECHO ALL An opening in the floor slides open.
      NEWITEM 8 72  VAL2=3613
      AFFECT 3613
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PUSH 1
    IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You push %a down into the hole.
      ECHO OTHERS %N pushes %a down into the hole.
      EQUAL ITEMVAL5 1
      AFFECT 3614
      ECHO ALL A rope ladder falls down from above, providing a way out!
      NEWITEM 0 1108 VAL2=3613
      AFFECT 3613
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB PULL 1
    IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You pull %a up from the hole, carefully coiling it up.
      ECHO OTHERS %N pulls %a up from the hole, carefully coiling it.
      ECHO PLAYER [Round: 10 seconds]
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
      EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
      AFFECT 3614
      ECHO ALL The rope ladder is hauled up, removing the only exit.
      REMOVEITEM 0
      AFFECT 3613
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB CLIMB 1
    IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You'll have to push it down in the hole first.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
NUMBER 3614
  NAME Oubliette
  *DESCRIPTION_START
Dirt and filth coat every surface of this deep, smooth pit. A small shelf seems to serve as both a bench and a bed, and a shallow hole in the corner is the only sign of sanitary facilities. The walls are way too smooth to climb, and the opening is too high up to jump for. Unless you can fly, you are probably stuck.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  FIXED_LIGHT
  IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER It smells really foul down here.
  ENDIF
NUMBER 3615
  NAME By an Oak Door
  *DESCRIPTION_START
A rough dirt passage comes to an end here at a thick oak door. You can hear occasional movement from the other side, though nothing from this one.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  FIXED_LIGHT
  EXIT N 3613
  ITEM 0 943  ADJ1=216  VAL1=5000  VAL2=3618  VAL3=3666
  IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO OTHERS %N listens to %h surroundings.
    ECHO PLAYER You hear occasional movement from beyond the oak door.
  ENDIF
NUMBER 3616
  NAME A Dirt Passage
  *DESCRIPTION_START
You stand at one end of a rough passage of loose dirt. A slight breeze blows in through a narrow hole in the far wall.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  FIXED_LIGHT
  ITEM 0 79  ADJ1=210  VAL2=358
  EXIT NW 3613
NUMBER 3617
  NAME A Dirt Passage
  *DESCRIPTION_START
This marks the end of a rough passage made of loose earth. A small opening here seems to open up into a wider room, but you can't get a good look from here.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  FIXED_LIGHT
  EXIT E 3613
  ITEM 0 72  ADJ1=294  VAL2=194
NUMBER 3618
  NAME Catacombs, Oak Door
  *DESCRIPTION_START
You stand within a small, relatively clean alcove in the passage. At the far end, stained with age and mildew, a huge carved oak door is set into the wall. An opening leads into the catacombs proper.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  FIXED_LIGHT
  ITEM 0 72  VAL2=424
  ITEM 1 943  ADJ1=216  VAL1=5000  VAL2=3615  VAL3=3666
NUMBER 3619
  NAME Last Resort, Roof
  *DESCRIPTION_START
You stand on the roof of the Last Resort, looking out over the city of Fayd. Your view of the north part of town is blocked by the huge Jewelry City Superstore, but other than that, the view is great. A small ladder in one corner leads back into the Resort proper. A long rope ladder tied here seems to lead to some kind of a balloon or blimp floating high above.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  OUTDOOR_FLOOR
  DAY_LIGHT
  ITEM 0 335  VAL2=3603
  EXIT U 3620
  IFPREVERB GAZE -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You gaze out across the city of Fayd, taking special note of the street just below.
    ECHO OTHERS %N gazes out over the city of Fayd.
    SHOWROOM 266
  ENDIF
  IFPREVERB HOWL -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You howl, letting the wind carry your voice across the entire city.
    ECHO OTHERS %N howls!
    AFFECT 266
    ECHO ALL You hear a long, eerie howl from the top of a nearby building.
  ENDIF
NUMBER 424
  NAME Catacombs
  *DESCRIPTION_START
Green, luminescent fungus grows all over the walls of this chamber. The light is eerie, moreover sickly, and you wonder how the fungus grows here. Perhaps it is due to the damp conditions which seem prevalent in this area.
  *DESCRIPTION_END
  INDOOR_FLOOR
  PARTIAL_DARKNESS
  ITEM 0 327  ADJ1=538
  ITEM 1 72  ADJ1=159  VAL2=3618
  EXIT NW 425
  EXIT E 408
